post_text:
Ms. Klasen's 6th-grade class spent a lot of time dancing and singing in the 2019-20 school year. They became masters at the "Waka Waka" Just Dance video, one of Ms. Klasen's favorites. They also spent many days listening to music. Of the many sing-alongs they had, one that everyone sang along too was Thomas Rhett's, "Look What God Gave Her." Claire Lecy put a spin to the song that fit the class much better! The class's intentions were to do a "flash mob" during lunch singing their new version of Thomas Rhett's song and using the dance from "Waka Waka." Due to COVID, they had to try it over Zoom. Not the performance they hoped for, but the lyrics are very worthy of sharing. Impressive writing done by Claire Lecy and dancing by Ms. Klasen's 6th-grade class. In speaking with Claire about the flash mob, she stated, "The process of putting the flash mob together really made a strong connection with the whole class and brought us all together."
https://youtu.be/NL_gBjKwXRI

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1_DxvQNmikEv1uMLiaep7Lh0luu3g3jSnTgNzmUCAWB8/edit?usp=sharing

YOUTUBE.COM
Look what Klasen gave' em

Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household.

Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.

Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

New On-site Class--Drone Racing and Battle Drones!
Spend an exciting day learning to drive drones, and then racing and/or battling them!

Drone Racing: Students will learn from an experienced drone pilot to complete challenges and earn their Drone Pilotâ€™s License.Once certified, students will compete against each other in various aerial obstacle courses and races. Students will work with and against each other in various competitive tournaments that will strengthen their teamwork skills.

Battle Drones: Students will learn from an experienced drone pilot to complete challenges and earn their Drone Pilotâ€™s License. Once certified, students will take to the skies with their new flying skills and compete with each other in exciting, aerial laser tag battles. Students will work with their teams and use their critical thinking skills to develop strategies for each aerial competition thrown their way.

Register Now! https://district745.ce.eleyo.com/search?redirected_yet=true&sf[category]=67

Childcare Update
Albany Area Schools will continue to provide necessary care for families who fall under the Tier 1 worker category, under the state's direction. Tier 1 workers now include healthcare and public health; law enforcement, public safety and first responders; food and agriculture; Judicial Branch (essential services); National Guard; educators and school staff; and childcare providers.

Please note that this care is intended for extreme circumstances in which no parent or guardian is available to care for a child, due to employment as a critical worker.

If you require care between March 30 and April 9, please complete the form below and a member of our team will be in touch with you.

https://forms.gle/s9ofFNqAmTpaWVtB8

post_text:
We have many exceptional students here at AAHS! Here are some that have been showing a lot of GRIT this quarter.

Liam, Alex, John, and Mya were all recognized by Mr. Eichten in Weight Training and Conditioning class.
Liam works extremely hard and is a true leader, Alex perseveres through difficult challenges, John works extremely hard and leads by example, and Mya is an exemplary student and shows excellent work ethic.

Selena was recognized by Mrs. Vanderhagen in American Lit 2. She regularly goes above and beyond and is a great role model for the power of perseverance and positivity.

Lily was recognized by Mrs. Curtis in Pottery class. She has been trying some very complicated pieces and has encountered quite a few setbacks. She uses these "bumps" as learning tools and keeps on pushing forward.

Kyle was also recognized by Mrs. Curtis in Drawing class. He works hard every day. He stays on task, tries his best, and approaches each assignment with a positive attitude.

Way to go, Huskies! #purplepride #AAHSlearns
